STANDARD OUT (1) : 

    CREATE EMPTY FILE : > Filename

    OVERWRITE WITH REDIRECTION : echo New Message > Filename

    APPEND AT ENDING OF FILE WITH REDIRECTION : echo New Message >> Filename


STANDARD IN (0) :
    
    REDIRECT INPUT TO COMMAND : command < Filename


STANDARD ERROR (2) : 

    REDIRECT ERROR MESSAGES TO FILE : commands 2> Filename

    REDIRECT BOTH ERROR AND OUTPUT : commands &> Filename

    DISCARD ALL INPUTS : commands &> /dev/null


CAT : 

    READ FILES : cat file_1 file_2 file_N
    
    ADD LINE NUMBER : cat -n Filename


MORE : 

    READ FILE IN PARTED MANNER : more Filename


LESS :

    READ FILE IN PAGED MANNER : less Path/To/File

    QUIT LESS MODE : q

    SEARCH IN LESS MODE : /KeyWord

    
HEAD & TAIL : 

    SEE FIRST N LINES IN FILE : head -n N Path/To/File

    SEE LAST N LINES IN FILE : tail -n N Path/To/File

    SEE LIVE UPDATES AT ENDING OF FILE : tail -f Path/To/File




    